Congrats on the bike - I've been riding a few years now myself so please do these things!! Get some leather gloves (if you can) asap.  I know you're in a desert but if you should fall the first thing usually to hit the ground is your hands - it is instinctive. Even at 20 MPH the asphalt will act like a cheese grater and strip the flesh off your palms. Practice quick stops by using the back brake first then squeezing SLOWLY and EVENLY with the front brake. 70% of your stopping power is in the front brakes. Don't wait until you have to do a quick stop - you need muscle memory in case you panic - needs to be automatic. I know not much traffic there but you could come upon a hole or a rock suddenly. Start watching videos by MC Rider or Motojitsu. They have beginner videos to learn from. Ride safely!

Ride safe Eva. There's two kinds of riders, those who've fallen and those who will fall.


Helmet and jacket help. Learning how to fall is also helpful. Safe travels!
